.. _getting_started:

***************
Getting started
***************
This section describes how to get CVXPY up and running.

.. _requirements:

Requirements
============

The current version of CVXPY requires `Python 2.6 <http://www.python.org/download/releases/2.6.6/>`_, `Python 2.7 <http://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7.1/>`_ or `Python 3.2 <http://www.python.org/download/releases/3.2.3/>`_ and the following packages:

* `CVXOPT <http://abel.ee.ucla.edu/cvxopt/>`_
* `Numpy <http://numpy.scipy.org/>`_
* `Scipy <http://www.scipy.org/>`_

.. _download:

Download
========
You can check out CVXPY from `here <http://code.google.com/p/cvxpy/>`_ using `svn <http://subversion.apache.org/>`_. Please keep in mind that this project is still in its development stage and future interface changes are possible.

.. _install:

Installation
============
To install CVXPY, execute the following command inside the directory that contains the file ``setup.py``::
   
     > sudo python setup.py install
